The South African company said its headline earnings were likely to jump by between 83% and 103%, or 2,715 cents and 3,010 cents per share. JOHANNESBURG – The world’s No.1 platinum miner Anglo American Platinum said on Tuesday it expects an up to two-fold rise in annual profit, helped by higher prices and improved operational performance. The South African company said its headline earnings were likely to jump by between 83% and 103%, or 2,715 cents and 3,010 cents per share. Headline EPS is the main profit measure in South Africa that strips out certain one-off items.